HEADWORD: Enclose
<hw>En*close"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>enclos</ets>, p. p. of <ets>enclore</ets> to enclose; pref.
<ets>en-</ets> (L. <ets>in</ets>) + <ets>clore</ets> to close. See
<er>Close</er>, and cf. <er>Inclose</er>, <er>Include</er>.]</ety>
<def>To inclose. See <er>Inclose</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

